The paper deals with efficient approximate answers to aggregate queries over large data sets, which is a common problem in data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). The focus on variance optimization and sampling schemes also suggests a connection to machine learning and statistics (cs.LG) and signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the use of weighted items and subset sums is a classic problem in discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
